<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Key F (1 flat). Hymn-tune style with mostly whole-note/half-note chords.
- F: F2-C3-F3-A3; Bb: Bb2-F3-Bb3-D4; C/C7: C2-G2-C3-E3 (+ Bb for C7).
- B° and Gm7 passing chords in bar 7 provide modal color.
- RH: 2-note thirds, mostly half-notes matching LH.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Clear I-IV-V-I cadences throughout
- Bars 7-8: B°-Gm7-C chromatic preparation for C cadence
- Bars 13-14: Bb color before final F cadence

TEXTURE ARC:
- Bars 1-8: Stately half-note chords, establishing F tonic
- Bars 9-12: More motion with C7 dominant
- Bars 13-16: Final cadential arch, full F close
-->
